Submitted By:            Combined: Douglas R. Reno (build fix) + still image + tune fix + clap fix + TD OBU fix
Date:                    2026-03-21
Initial Package Version: 1.21.2
Upstream Status:         Pending
Origin:                  Upstream (PR #1680) + four additional fixes
Description:             Fixes building libheif with SVT-AV1 4.0 and later.
                         Four changes on top of the original build fix:

                         1. Still image mode (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            avif=true, intra_period_length=-1, fps=1/1.

                         2. tune=SSIM fallback to PSNR (SVT-AV1 >= 4.0.0):
                            SVT-AV1 4.x requires CRF for tune=SSIM but libheif uses
                            CQP. Sharp passes tune=ssim by default which crashes the
                            encoder. Fall back silently to PSNR.

                         3. query_encoded_size=nullptr in plugin table (like AOM):
                            Prevents libheif from adding a clap box with fractional
                            pixel offsets for odd-dimension images. Internal calls to
                            svt_query_encoded_size remain for correct encoder padding.

                         4. Strip Temporal Delimiter OBU from output bitstream:
                            AVIF spec (ISO 23000-22 §2.1) forbids TD OBUs in image
                            items. SVT-AV1 in avif mode prepends one (2 bytes: 0x12
                            0x00). Firefox rejects such files. Strip it after encode.

